04/08/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- A car plowed into a crowded bus stop near the Ierapetra resort on the island of Crete Monday (August 3rd), injuring 16 people, most of them children. Witness told police the driver tried to pass another vehicle and lost control of the car, crashing into the bus stop where a team of young scouts and their instructors were waiting. (Kathimerini - 04/08/09; ENA - 03/08/09) 
